{% set pageTitle = 'DJs | Convergence 26 - Louisville, KY' %}

{% import '_macros/image.njk' as img %}

{% extends '_layouts/default.njk' %}

{% block main %}
   <div class="container">
      <div class="block">
         <h1 class="title">DJs</h1>

         <p>We’re pleased to announce the DJ lineup for Convergence 26…</p>

         <p>
            The Pirate Twins (Scary Lady Sarah & William Faith), DJ Azy & DJ MAUS (Obscura Undead), DJ Ichabod, DJ Mistress McCutchan, Philly Peroxide, DJ Skeletal, and Radio Arcane’s AndrOspore, Brian Drabant, DJ Kaleidoscope, Osiris Ani, & Sorrow-Vomit.
         </p>

         <p><em>Additional info coming soon...</em></p>

         <a class="btn" href="{{ tickets.eventbrite }}" target="_blank">Tickets Now Available</a>

         <br>

         <article id="pirate-twins" class="band">
            <h2 class="band__title">The Pirate Twins</h2>

            <figure class="band__figure">
               {{ img.picture(
                  jpg="/images/djs/pirate-twins.jpg",
                  webp="/images/djs/pirate-twins.webp",
                  alt="The Pirate Twins",
                  className="band__img"
               ) }}
            </figure>

            <div class="band__bio">
               <p>The Pirate Twins are the DJ team of Scary Lady Sarah and William Faith.</p>

               <p>The duo have spun at events all over North America and Europe, with annual appearances at Wave-Gotik-Treffen in Leipzig, Germany. Sarah—who also spun at C1, C5, C6, the “C7 Rescue,” C8, C9, C10, C12, C19, C20, C21, and C23—has been a professional working club DJ since 1988, and her bi-monthly club night, Nocturna, is now in its 32nd year.</p>

               <p>The Pirate Twins spin a wide variety of music, including, but not limited to—current and classic post-punk, Goth, industrial, punk, glam, deathrock, ethereal, ambient, shoegaze, new wave, EBM, darkwave, dark indie, and more.</p>
            </div>

            <footer class="band__links">
               <a href="https://www.facebook.com/thepiratetwins" target="_blank" title="The Pirate Twins @ Facebook">
                  <img src="/images/icons/facebook-square.svg" inline class="icon" />
               </a>
            </footer>
         </article>
			
			<article id="pirate-twins" class="band">
            <h2 class="band__title">DJ Azy and DJ Maus (Obscura Undead)</h2>

            <figure class="band__figure">
               {{ img.lazyPic(
                  jpg="/images/djs/obscura-undead.jpg",
                  webp="/images/djs/obscura-undead.webp",
                  alt="DJ Azy and DJ Maus (Obscura Undead)",
                  className="band__img"
               ) }}
            </figure>

            <div class="band__bio">
               <p>Azy and Maus run Obscura Undead, a Florida-based collective of DJs and creators devoted to spreading new Goth, post-punk, darkwave, minimal wave, and deathrock. Maus specializes in synth driven post-punk and wave, while Azy’s focus is guitar-driven Goth and deathrock.</p>
            </div>

            <footer class="band__links">
